    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - GAUGE CLUSTERS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GAUGE CLUSTERS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The gauge clusters are injection molded housings which have an integral stamped circuit plate. The
                clusters provide locations for various gauges, warning lights, and indicator lights. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>
                for the circuit path of the left gauge cluster, and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>
                for the circuit path of the right gauge cluster.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0824518" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824518.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Left Gauge Cluster (Viewed From Rear of Housing)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WATER TEMPERATURE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ENGINE OIL PRESSURE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. VOLTMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. AIR RESTRICTION (OPTIONAL) OR AIR APPLICATION (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PYROMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. LEFT TURN SIGNAL/FLASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. POWER DIVIDER LOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. WATER TEMPERATURE (NOT USED)</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. ENGINE OIL PRESSURE (NOT USED)</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. COOLANT LEVEL (NOT USED)</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. REAR LIGHT (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. PARK BRAKE (NOT USED)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824519" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0824519.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Right Gauge Cluster (Viewed From Rear of Housing)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FORWARD REAR AXLE TEMPERATURE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR REAR AXLE TEMPERATURE (OPTIONAL) OR TRANSMISSION OIL PRESSURE (OPTIONAL)
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRANSMISSION OIL TEMPERATURE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. AIR PRESSURE (PRIMARY)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. AIR PRESSURE (SECONDARY)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FUEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. LOW AIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. RIGHT TURN SIGNAL/FLASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. OIL/WATER (CUMMINS M11, N14 and ISM ENGINES ONLY)</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. AIR SUSPENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. ENGINE WARNING</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. ENGINE STOP</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. ENGINE SHUTDOWN (NOT USED)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cluster Power and Connection</title>
            <para>Proper connector insertion and power to cluster is assured if the following indicators react when the
                key switch is turned on:
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To ensure full power to all instruments in the clusters, connector lock tabs on both sides of
                        harness connector must be solidly engaged with cluster socket.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Voltmeter pointer moves up scale.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Some warning lights come on (depends on installation).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Electrical gauges indicate zero.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>With power to cluster off, electric gauge pointers may move to any point on the gauge scale. This is
                inherent to the gauges and does not indicate a faulty part.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Circuit Plate Testing</title>
            <para>Procedures for testing the gauge clusters, warning lights and indicator lights are given in the
                troubleshooting table for each warning or indicator light.
            </para>
            <para>If a gauge cluster must be replaced, obtain a new cluster housing and transfer all components to the
                new housing.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Small diodes are also located in some circuits. Note the polarity (direction of current flow)
                        through these diodes when making a circuit continuity check.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
